<dl id="n12063e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12063e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12063e"> 63(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ambrose &amp; Merlin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Au cinqui&egrave;me si&egrave;cle de notre &egrave;re naissait dans l&apos;&icirc;le des Bretons un enfant qui devait &ecirc;tre, comme Domitius, un po&euml;te c&eacute;l&egrave;bre, et voir joindre &agrave; son nom d&apos;Ambroise le surnom de Marzin ou Merlin <br><font color="green">[In the fifth century of our era on the island of the Bretons a child was born who, like Domitius, would become a famous poet, and who would see the name of <mark>Marzin or Merlin added to his given name Ambrose</mark>]</font> <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 27-28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
